formula: G.f. (Prod_{k>0} 1 + x^k)^8.Given g.f. A(x), then B(q) = q*A(q^3) satisfies 0 = f(B(q), B(q^2)) where f(u, v) = -u^2 + v + 16*u*v^2. - _Michael Somos_, May 29 2004Expansion of q^(-1/3) * (eta(q^2) / eta(q))^8 in powers of q.Euler transform of period 2 sequence [ 8, 0, ...]. - _Michael Somos_, Jun 06 2005Expansion of chi(-x)^-8 in powers of x where chi() is a Ramanujan theta function.a(n) ~ exp(2 * Pi * sqrt(2*n/3)) / (16 * 2^(3/4) * 3^(1/4) * n^(3/4)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Mar 05 2015
mathematica: a[ n_] := SeriesCoefficient[ QPochhammer[ -x, x]^8, {x, 0, n}]; (* _Michael Somos_, Feb 22 2015 *)
prog: (PARI) {a(n) = local(A); if( n<0, 0, A = x * O(x^n); polcoeff( (eta(x^2 + A) / eta(x + A))^8, n))}; /* _Michael Somos_, May 29 2004 */
